This paper is about designing a recurrent neural network (RNN) acoustic model for speech recognition that can effectively utilize future contextual information while keeping the model latency and computation cost low. This topic falls under the intersection of several sub-fields of computer science, including natural language processing (NLP), machine learning (ML), and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers research on NLP and ML. 

The second likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound), which focuses on research related to audio and speech processing. The third likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers research on various ML techniques, including RNNs. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which covers research on various AI techniques, including speech recognition.
